Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nicole M Williams in court.  Attorney Gerardo Antonio De Los Santos Jr in court for Nicole M Williams.  Prosecuting attorney Katherine Seelow for Nicholas Heitman in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Arraignment. Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. Case adjourned to Br. 36.  Status conference scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Nicole M Williams in court in person.  Attorney Gerardo Antonio De Los Santos Jr in court in person for Nicole M Williams.  Attorney Nicolas J Heitman appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: West Allis PD Detective D. Madden. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed. Case is adjourned to Branch 36.
Arraignment scheduled for October 5, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Nicole M Williams in court, appear in person  with attorney Gerardo Antonio De Los Santos.  Nicolas Heitman appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. State witness present. Attorney De Los Santos needs more time to meet with client. Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Motion to postpone preliminary hearing; filed.

Defendant Nicole M Williams in court with attorney Jason A Findling.  Defendant Nicole M Williams in custody.  Sara Beth Hill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Nicole M Williams appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Wagner, Branch 38.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS NOT INDIGENT. This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Nicole M Williams not in court.  Paul Leonard Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 05/23/2022@2pm
